== 槍械文化 ==
{{more|美國槍械暴力問題}}
[[File:US_Navy_100923-N-7682A-014_Navy_Junior_ROTC_cadets_from_Hamilton_High_School,_Ohio,_practice_marksmanship_at_the_Fire_Arms_Training_Simulator_(FATS.jpg|thumb]]
[[Image:Houston_Gun_Show_at_the_George_R._Brown_Convention_Center.jpg|thumb]]
[[美國的槍械文化|美國的槍械文化]]可以追溯到[[美國獨立戰爭|獨立戰爭]]，甚至以前的[[西部拓荒時代|拓荒時期]]，如經常成為電影背景的西部牛仔生活<ref name="SpitzerCh1">{{cite book|last=Spitzer|first=Robert J.|title=The Politics of Gun Control|year=1995|publisher=Chatham House|isbn=9781566430227|url=https://archive.org/details/politicsofguncon00spit}}</ref>。美國私人擁有配槍的比率冠絕全世界<ref>{{cite news| url= https://www.reuters.com/article/idUSL2834893820070828| title=U.S. most armed country with 90 guns per 100 people| publisher=[[Reuters|Reuters]] | date=August 28, 2007}}</ref>，將近一半的家庭擁有一支或以上的槍支<ref>{{cite news| url= http://www.gallup.com/poll/150353/self-reported-gun-ownership-highest-1993.aspx| title=Self-Reported Gun Ownership in the U.S. Is Highest Since 1993| website=Gallup.com | date=October 26, 2011}}</ref>，民眾的權利被受[[美國憲法第二修正案|第二修正案]]所保障<ref>{{ cite news| url=https://www.supremecourt.gov/opinions/07pdf/07-290.pdf| title=US District of Columbia et al v Heller | publisher=US Supreme Court| date=June 26, 2008 }}</ref>。部分學校甚至要在大門設置[[金屬探測器|金屬探測器]]，防止學生帶槍上學<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/education/2021/12/10/school-metal-detectors-dont-work/|title=It’s time to revisit metal detectors in schools|date=2021-12-10|publisher=The Washington Post|author=Valerie Strauss}}</ref>。

== 美國人的世界觀 ==
美國民眾當中大約有三分之一未曾擁有過[[美国护照|護照]]，意味著他們未曾離開過美國國境<ref>{{cite web|url=https://today.yougov.com/topics/travel/articles-reports/2021/04/21/only-one-third-americans-have-valid-us-passport|title=Only one-third of Americans have a valid US passport|publisher=YouGovAmerica|author=Kathy Frankovic|date=2021-04-22}}</ref>。

